# Quick MCP Configuration Template

## Copy this to your MCP configuration file

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "supabase": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-supabase"],
      "env": {
        "SUPABASE_URL": "REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_PROJECT_URL",
        "SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY": "REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY"
      }
    },
    "github": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-github"],
      "env": {
        "GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN": "REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Steps to Configure:

1. **Get Supabase Credentials**:
   - Go to https://supabase.com
   - Create project "growmind"
   - Settings → API
   - Copy Project URL and service_role key

2. **Get GitHub Token**:
   - Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
   - Generate new token (classic)
   - Select scopes: repo, workflow, packages
   - Copy token

3. **Update Configuration**:
   - Replace REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_PROJECT_URL
   - Replace REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
   - Replace REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN

4. **Save & Restart**:
   - Save the configuration file
   - Restart your AI assistant
   - MCP servers should now be available!

## Verify It Works:

Ask your AI assistant:
- "Can you list my Supabase tables?"
- "Can you check my GitHub repositories?"

If you get responses, MCP is working! 🎉
